    %h2 The Story
    
    %p When I thought about doing this, I put together some loose plans, but didn't have any dates/times lined up with people/places. I wanted to be able to do that in real-time and leave some room open for adventure. You know.. maybe I will randomly meet people and get to see some amazing places I didn't intend.
    
    %p While that seemed like the right thing to do, next time I will try and line up at least my first day. However, I did get to experience some unexpected magic! Day one was all about planning. I spent the day trying to line up some of the specifics: where would I go, when would I get there, who would meet with me when I get there kind of stuff.
    
    %h3 The Magic Bus
    
    %p I hopped on the 14x bus from Outer Mission to SOMA. I wanted to visit software product companies, and so it just made sense that I try and land a spot there. I figured, I'm on East coast time and up early here... I'll find a coffee shop, get charged, open my laptop and line some stuff up.
    
    %h3 Coffee or Chemistry?
    
    %p When I got off the bus, I fired up Yelp and searched for coffee. Saw that there was a #{link_to "Blue Bottle", "http://www.bluebottlecoffee.com/locations/mint-cafe/"} coffee shop and had heard good things, so I walked there. Holy shit! I ordered a small pot of a single roast African Gamayo and watched as they stirred something over a Bunsen burner-like contraption with vessels that looked like lab glass. The dude working the fire was obviously caffeinated and very into what he was doing. When I got my pot of coffee, it came in a stand holding a small florence flask of hot bean juice and the coffee cup was also resembling of sort of beaker. It came with instructions as to when the optimal temperature would be to drink this fine nectar. The only thing that was missing was a thermometer... and maybe safety goggles. I joke around.. but the coffee was amazing. This was foreshadowing for how coffee in San Francisco was to ruin coffee for me for at least the next two weeks!
    
    %p
