    %h3 What a Minute, I Know this Place!
    
    %p I started to walk back to Mission St. to get on the bus. Then I thought... wait a minute, I know this place! See, a long while back I lived out here in SF to go to the San Francisco Art Institute. I used to visit the #{link_to "Museum of Modern Art", "http://sfmoma.org"} all the time. It was right across the street. And I didn't want to pass up the chance to take a walk through.
    
    %p (NOTE: The last 30 minutes of every day at the MOMA is free. If you're in the area at that time, you should go.)
    
    %p There was only an hour left to check out the collection, but it was enough. Well, there could never really be enough time to look at all the work there. But it was at least enough time for me to walk in and I cried, I smiled, my jaw was dropped. See, this may sound harsh, but I feel sometimes that life would be shit without art. Going to the museum made me want to make everything I do matter, make everything count! 
    
    %p It was a great end to day 1.
    
